## 12. Security & Privacy Architecture

### 12.1 Data Privacy Guarantee
This application is designed to minimize privacy risks. **No user data is transmitted to external servers.** Business data exists solely on the user's local device. There is no backend, no API, and no analytics SDK.

> This architecture inherently reduces (but does not eliminate) GDPR/CCPA compliance risks. Merchants are still responsible for the physical security of their device.

### 12.2 Permissions
| Permission | Purpose | Method | Scope |
|---|---|---|---|
| Camera | Barcode scanning | `navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia` | In-session only, not stored |
| Notifications | Backup reminders + update alerts | `Notification.requestPermission()` | Via Service Worker |
| Persistent Storage | Prevent IndexedDB eviction | `navigator.storage.persist()` | Flags DB as persistent with OS |
| Audio | UI sound effects | `AudioContext` | Local playback only |

### 12.3 Data Backup Encryption
v1.x: Backup files are plain JSON (`.msbos`). The file extension communicates the file type to the user.  
**Planned for Phase 2:** AES-256 password-protected encryption before download, via the WebCrypto API.

### 12.4 Update Integrity
App updates are delivered via standard HTTPS to the hosting provider. The Service Worker caches assets with SHA hashes to ensure tamper detection. No user data is touched during an update.

