## 17. Error Handling

### 17.1 Database Errors
| Scenario | Behavior |
|---|---|
| IndexedDB unavailable | Falls back to `localStorage` for KV operations |
| Storage quota exceeded | `navigator.storage.estimate()` result displayed as a warning |
| Corrupted backup import | Schema validation throws; user sees error alert |

### 17.2 User-Facing Error States
| Error | Message Shown |
|---|---|
| Empty cart checkout | "Your cart is empty" (UI-level block) |
| Notification denied | "Notification permission denied or blocked by browser settings." |
| Camera denied | Barcode scanner shows manual entry fallback |
| Restore invalid file | "Invalid backup file. This is not an Ultimate Backup file." |
| Backup export failed | "Failed to export backup." |

### 17.3 React Error Boundary
No global error boundary exists in v1.x. Fatal React errors (e.g., undefined icon components) cause full app crash. Each screen should implement a local `ErrorBoundary` in Phase 2.

